---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Connect with Us | Doctoral College UK" description="Get in touch with Doctoral College UK — enquire about programmes, book a conversation, explore partnerships, or follow us on social media.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Get in Touch</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Connect with Doctoral College UK</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">Whether you are exploring doctoral study for the first time, ready to apply, looking to collaborate, or seeking information on behalf of an organisation — we would love to hear from you.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact Options -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

        <!-- Enquiries -->
        <div class="card">
          <p class="section-label mb-3">General Enquiries</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Email Us</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-6">For all general enquiries about our programmes, admissions, fees, or events, please email our team directly. We aim to respond to all enquiries within two working days.</p>
          <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Admissions &amp; Programmes</p>
              <a href="mailto:admissions@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">admissions@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Student Support &amp; Welfare</p>
              <a href="mailto:support@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">support@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Research &amp; Publications</p>
              <a href="mailto:research@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">research@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Events &amp; Symposium</p>
              <a href="mailto:events@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">events@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">We do not operate a telephone helpline, but if a call would be more helpful, our team can arrange this via email.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Book a Call -->
        <div class="card">
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Prospective Researchers</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Book a Conversation</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-6">If you are considering a doctoral programme with DCUK, the best next step is a 30-minute online conversation with a member of our academic team. This is an informal, no-obligation discussion — not an interview — designed to help you understand whether a DCUK programme is right for you.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-6">In a booking conversation, we can discuss your research interests, help identify the most appropriate programme, explain the application process, and answer any questions you have about study alongside professional life.</p>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted">To book a conversation, email <a href="mailto:admissions@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">admissions@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a> with the subject line <strong>"Book a Conversation"</strong>. Include a brief note on your research interests and your preferred availability. We will respond within two working days with options.</p>
          </div>
          <a href="mailto:admissions@doctoralcollege.ac.uk?subject=Book%20a%20Conversation" class="btn-primary">Book a conversation</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Partnerships -->
        <div class="card">
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Organisations</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Partnership Enquiries</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">DCUK works with organisations across the public, private, and third sectors on a range of partnership arrangements. These include employer sponsorship schemes, corporate research partnerships, consultancy projects, and institutional collaboration on doctoral development programmes.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">If your organisation is looking to invest in the research capacity of senior staff, or to commission applied research on a specific organisational challenge, we would welcome a conversation.</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-sm mb-6">
            <p class="font-medium">Partnership opportunities include:</p>
            <ul class="text-muted list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
              <li>Employer doctoral sponsorship schemes (group discounts available)</li>
              <li>Organisational research partnerships</li>
              <li>Bespoke research training and methods workshops</li>
              <li>Consultancy and applied research projects</li>
              <li>Supervisor development for HEI partners</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <a href="mailto:research@doctoralcollege.ac.uk?subject=Partnership%20Enquiry" class="btn-outline">Discuss a partnership</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Social & Media -->
        <div class="card">
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Follow &amp; Connect</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Social Media &amp; Media Enquiries</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-6">Follow DCUK to stay connected with news, research insights, event announcements, and the work of our doctoral community.</p>
          <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-surface border border-border rounded flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">in</div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold">LinkedIn</p>
                <a href="https://linkedin.com/company/doctoral-college-uk" class="text-accent text-sm hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin.com/company/doctoral-college-uk</a>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-surface border border-border rounded flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">X</div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold">X / Twitter</p>
                <a href="https://x.com/DoctoralCollegeUK" class="text-accent text-sm hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@DoctoralCollegeUK</a>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-surface border border-border rounded flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">YT</div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold">YouTube</p>
                <a href="https://youtube.com/@DoctoralCollegeUK" class="text-accent text-sm hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">youtube.com/@DoctoralCollegeUK</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">For media enquiries, interview requests, or press information, please email <a href="mailto:media@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">media@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Address / Info -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Registered Address</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Doctoral College UK<br/>
          Suite 4, Cavendish House<br/>
          12 King Street<br/>
          London<br/>
          EC2V 8AJ</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Response Times</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">We aim to respond to all email enquiries within two working days. During our Admissions peak periods (January–March and August–October) response times may be slightly longer. We will always acknowledge your email promptly.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Complaints</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">If you have a concern or complaint about DCUK, please email <a href="mailto:quality@doctoralcollege.ac.uk" class="text-accent hover:underline">quality@doctoralcollege.ac.uk</a>. We take all feedback seriously and will follow our formal complaints procedure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
